snippet: Alberto Contador, a five-time Grand Tour winner, won the Tirreno-Adriatico to signal a return to form after not recording a multistage victory last year.
abstract: Five-time Grand Tour winner Alberto Contador signals a return to form by winning the weeklong Tirreno-Adriatico bicycle race in Italy.
lead_paragraph: Alberto Contador, a five-time Grand Tour winner, won the Tirreno-Adriatico to signal a return to form after not recording a multistage victory last year.

headline.main: Contador Wins Weeklong Race in Italy
